      "id": "687668",
      "is_folded": false,
      "answerer": {
        "username": "Nederland",
        "uid": "73269"
      },
      "contents": "<div class=\"markitup-box aw-briefly\">\n\t\t\t通过关键词，我认为原文应是这篇：<a href=\"url/link/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cucG9saXRpY28uZXUvYXJ0aWNsZS9ldXJvcGUtdGVjaC1zb3ZlcmVpZ250eS1jaGluYS1wZXRlci13ZW5uaW5rLWFzbWwv\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://www.politico.eu/article/europe-tech-sovereignty-china-peter-wennink-asml/\">https://www.politico.eu/article/europe-tech-sovereignty-china-peter-wennink-asml/</a><br/>\n略看一眼之后，得出结论：<mark>支人</mark>又在曲解英语！<br/>\n<blockquote>\"If you shut out the Chinese with export control measures, you'll force them to strive toward <b>tech sovereignty</b>, in their case real tech sovereignty ... In 15 years' time they'll be able to do it all by themselves — and their market [for European suppliers] will be gone,\" Wennink told POLITICO on the top floor of ASML's towering building in Veldhoven, a town in the southeast of the country.</blockquote><br/>\ntech sovereignty是指科技自主，它是个很模糊的词语，结合上下文可知，形容对象不是指芯片技术，而是整体对于科技产业“high-end tech”部分的泛泛而谈（见文章开头记者采访的议题），那么接下来看看Wennink是怎么解释的：<br/>\n<blockquote>\"Sovereignty means you have the freedom to do what you think is necessary to allow a responsible society to flourish. You gain this freedom by <b>having a bargaining chip</b> that's so big that others have to listen to you,\" Wennink said.<br/>\n<br/>\nIn other words: \"You have to have something that others need.\" </blockquote><br/>\n这下知道<mark>支那</mark>媒体的说法是怎么来的吧？Bargaining chip在英语里是指有利因素、谈判筹码，<b>这是固有的习语</b>，又不是指芯片的那个“chip”，人家根本就不是说中国要打破光刻机科技！<br/>\n<br/>\n可怜的小粉红，在习大大“东升西降”精神的影响下与外界与世隔绝，又不谙英语，只能被这种无良媒体和赤匪的造谣蒙在鼓里，还以为自己赢麻了。\t\t<div class=\"aw-stretch-content-button-container\"><button class=\"aw-stretch-content-button\" type=\"button\"></button></div></div>",
      "date": "2023-09-09",
      "agree_count": 3,
      "discussion_count": 0,
      "discussions": []
    },
